description.undefined: This ontology models the Food domain. It allows to describe ingredients and food products.

An ingredient : a certain quantity of food that is part of another food

comment.undefined:
Represents an ingredient line in a recipe (for a Dish) or an ingredient listed in the ingredient list (for a Product).

We need to specify a quantity and unit, so the relation is not binary. So the value for the containsIngredient property of a Food object is an object of the IngredientAmount class (instead of a Food object or string directly). See http://www.w3.org/TR/swbp-n-aryRelations/ for details.

label.undefined: Anything that can be eaten: a basic Food item (e.g. salt), a Dish made with a recipe, a manufactured Food Product
Recipe

comment.undefined: A recipe as a set of ingredients together with the protocol to prepare the resulting food

label.undefined: A manufactured food product
Text of the list of ingredients

comment.undefined: Full text of the list of ingredients of a Food item (Product or Dish). May contain more details than what can be listed in the containsIngredient properties.
